[[File:Reverse of stater of Anted (FindID 75086).jpg|thumb|right|Reverse of [[stater]] of Antedios]] [[File:An Iron Age Gold stater of Anted Iceni Celtic Coin Index reference, 3.0438 (FindID 293110).jpg|thumb|right|An Iron Age Gold stater of Anted]] '''Anted''' is the name of the coins issued by [[Antedios]] (or Anted), an ancient king of the Iceni, a Brythonic tribe who inhabited the present day county of Norfolk in Britain from approximately the 1st century BCE until the 1st century CE.
Only the first five letters appears on his coinage, the ending -ios is conjectural.<ref>[http://homepages.rpi.edu/~holmes/Hobbies/Genealogy2/ps31/ps31_478.htm Antedios (Anted) King Of Iceni], homepages.rpi.edu</ref>
