Most human civilizations - [[History of India|India]], [[History of China|China]], [[Ancient Egypt|Egypt]], [[Ancient Near East|Mesopotamia]], [[Maya civilization|Maya]], and [[Inca Empire|Inca]], among others - based their culture on complex systems of [[astrology]], which provided a link between the cosmos with the conditions and events on earth.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Ayurvedic Astrology: Self-healing Through the Stars|last=Frawley|first=David|publisher=Lotus Press|year=2005|isbn=8120831349|location=Twin Lakes, Wisconsin|pages=3}}</ref> For these, the astrological practice was not mere divination because it also served as the foundation for their spiritual culture and knowledge-systems used for practical purposes such as the calendar (see [[Mesoamerica|Mesoamerican]] calendrical shamans<ref>{{Cite book|title=Astrology through History: Interpreting the Stars from Ancient Mesopotamia to the Present|last=Burns|first=William|publisher=ABC-CLIO|year=2018|isbn=9781440851421|location=Santa Barbara, CA|pages=225}}</ref>) and medicine (e.g. ''[[I Ching]]''). Astrological tradition even contributed to the development of [[astronomy]] as the study of the skies provided invaluable insights about celestial bodies. For instance, the [[Ptolemaic Kingdom|Ptolemaic]] astrological tradition has already listed some of the planets in the [[Solar System|solar system]] and their movements.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Sefer Ḥakhmoni|last=Mancuso|first=Piergabriele|publisher=BRILL|year=2010|isbn=9789004167629|location=Leiden|pages=321}}</ref>
The following is an ''incomplete'' list of the different traditions, types, systems, methods, applications, and branches of astrology.
==Current traditions== Traditions still practiced in modern times include: *[[Burmese Zodiac|Burmese astrology]] *[[Chinese astrology]] *[[Electional astrology]] *[[Horary astrology]] *[[Horoscopic astrology]] **[[Natal astrology]] *[[Indian astrology]] ** [[Sidereal astrology]] *[[Sri Lankan Astrology (Sinhalese Astrology)]] *[[Tibetan astrology]] *[[Western astrology]] **[[Tropical astrology]]
==Historical traditions== Traditions which were once widely used but have either partly or fully fallen into disuse: *[[Agricultural astrology]] *[[Arab and Persian astrology]] and [[Islamic astrology]] *[[Babylonian astrology]] *[[Early Irish astrology|Celtic astrology]] *[[Astrology in Hellenistic Egypt|Egyptian astrology]] *[[Hellenistic astrology]] *[[Hindu astrology]] *[[Judicial astrology]] *[[Katarchic astrology]] *[[Maya calendar|Mayan astrology]] *[[Medical astrology]] *[[Meteorological astrology]] *[[Mundane astrology]] *[[Nadi astrology]] *[[Political astrology]]
==Recent Western developments== Traditions which have arisen relatively recently in the West: *[[Cosmobiology]] *[[Financial astrology]] *[[Hamburg School of Astrology]] *[[Heliocentric astrology]] *[[Huber School of Astrology]] *[[Locational astrology]] **[[Astrocartography]] *[[Psychological astrology]] *[[Sun sign astrology]] *[[Synoptical astrology]]
==Esoteric systems of astrology== Astrological concepts applied to various [[esoteric]] schools of thought or forms of [[divination]]: *[[Classical planets in Western alchemy|Alchemy and astrology]] **[[Astrology and the classical elements]] *[[Chiromancy]] *[[Christianity and astrology]] *[[Esoteric astrology]] *[[Geomancy]] *[[Kabbalistic astrology]] *[[Astrology and numerology|Numerology]] *[[Physiognomy]] **[[Phrenology]] *[[Rosicrucian]]ism *[[I Ching]] *[[Tarot reading|Tarot divination]]
